100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 8, 1926, the United States Supreme Court ruled that the government could not impose taxes on the income of state and local governments, a significant decision impacting state finances. In Europe, a coalition of German parties successfully united to form a new government aimed at stabilizing the country amidst ongoing economic challenges. Meanwhile, in the arts, the first performance of George Gershwin's "Rhapsody in Blue" was celebrated, blending classical and jazz influences and marking a pivotal moment in American music.
